idk I like to post and check in with myself when I feel this way to help keep this dialog in my head on a healthy track, and I want yall to know that with positive reinforcement, yall have been helping with this process (:

I slept in comfy all alone on my mattress on the floor today, and woke up the most comfortable I've ever felt in the morning in years. I dont remember the last time I wasn't banking on coffee to motivate me away from ideation or ruminative thought spirals. I feel human.

I have time to think about the things I want to do with my life, I have time to feel like despite the future shrinking, it's not going away tomorrow. I have time to sit around and just rest and do nothing in the present moment because I just want to.

and that space in my thoughts, that I would spend fixating on whether or not I was doing everything I could for whoever needs me, is being spent on just being enough for who wants me there. in what ways I can be. it's liberating, I have so much more space for creativity.

posting this rn in a moment of clarity after talking down an escalation with my ex, and being close with so many friends I've met online enough to meet them in person and send them Christmas cards and shit... like im not full of nearly as much self loathing or uncertainty.

idk spending every other day getting drunk, hoping the hurting people I poured my time into would heal with me, not having the strength to pull myself and someone else out of it, then needing to pull away entirely on more than one occasion, learning to do that with grace...

I feel happy with who I am as a person rn, it's taken me years to wake up in the morning and not regret or question every choice I make, and each day in my newer spaces, it's been getting easier and easier to see myself as making progress from who I was.
